    <hr xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"/>
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="note"><p class="Body-content-no-indent">The amount of money that Sally saves per week stays  <b>constant</b>. The relationship therefore has a  <b>constant rate of             change</b>.</p>

            <p>With every friend that joins, the number of
chocolates per friend changes. The number of
chocolates changes (decreases)  <b>rapidly at first
and then it changes slower</b>. The  <b>rate of
change is not constant</b>.</p>
<p>
The amount that Vusi would like to earn per bag
of acorns grows faster and faster with each bag
that he collects. The  <b>rate of change increases</b>.
</p>
<p>The area of a square also  <b>increases more and
more</b> for every cm added to the side length.
</p>
            </div>

<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="aside">
<p>
The  <b>rate of change</b> means
how fast or slow change
happens per unit of time.</p>
</div>

<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="aside">
<p>The  <b>shape</b> of a bar graph shows
the  <b>rate of change</b> of the
relationship. If the rate of
change is constant, the shape
is a  <b>straight line</b>. If it is
changing, the shape is a  <b>curve</b>.</p>
</div>

